The paper focuses on the design strategies of experts in object-oriented programming, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) categories. The paper specifically discusses object-oriented design (cs.OO) and its comparison to procedural design. The implications of the results for Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HCI) systems are also discussed. Finally, the paper provides insight into the knowledge structures of experts, which could potentially fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) category.
